def quick_overview(df, name):
    """Display quick overview of a dataframe"""
    print(f"\n{'='*60}")
    print(f"OVERVIEW: {name}")
    print('='*60)
    print(f"Shape: {df.shape[0]:,} rows  {df.shape[1]} columns")
    print(f"\nMemory usage: {df.memory_usage(deep=True).sum() / 1024**2:.2f} MB")
    print(f"\nDuplicate rows: {df.duplicated().sum():,}")
    
    print(f"\nData types:")
    print(df.dtypes.value_counts())
    
    print(f"\nMissing values:")
    missing = df.isnull().sum()
    missing_pct = (missing / len(df)) * 100
    missing_df = pd.DataFrame({
        'Missing': missing[missing > 0],
        'Percentage': missing_pct[missing > 0]
    }).sort_values('Missing', ascending=False)
    
    if len(missing_df) > 0:
        print(missing_df)
    else:
        print("No missing values!")

# Overview of each table
quick_overview(orders, "Orders")
quick_overview(order_items, "Order Items")
quick_overview(customers, "Customers")
quick_overview(products, "Products")
quick_overview(reviews, "Reviews")

# Extract temporal features
orders['year'] = orders['order_purchase_timestamp'].dt.year
orders['month'] = orders['order_purchase_timestamp'].dt.month
orders['day'] = orders['order_purchase_timestamp'].dt.day
orders['hour'] = orders['order_purchase_timestamp'].dt.hour
orders['dayofweek'] = orders['order_purchase_timestamp'].dt.dayofweek
orders['date'] = orders['order_purchase_timestamp'].dt.date

# Daily orders
daily_orders = orders.groupby('date').size().reset_index(name='orders')
daily_orders['date'] = pd.to_datetime(daily_orders['date'])

fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(16, 10))

# Daily trend
axes[0, 0].plot(daily_orders['date'], daily_orders['orders'], linewidth=1, alpha=0.7)
axes[0, 0].set_title('Daily Orders Trend', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
axes[0, 0].set_xlabel('Date')
axes[0, 0].set_ylabel('Number of Orders')
axes[0, 0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)

# Monthly trend
monthly_orders = orders.groupby(['year', 'month']).size().reset_index(name='orders')
monthly_orders['period'] = monthly_orders['year'].astype(str) + '-' + monthly_orders['month'].astype(str).str.zfill(2)
axes[0, 1].plot(monthly_orders['period'], monthly_orders['orders'], marker='o', linewidth=2)
axes[0, 1].set_title('Monthly Orders Trend', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
axes[0, 1].set_xlabel('Month')
axes[0, 1].set_ylabel('Number of Orders')
axes[0, 1].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
axes[0, 1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)

# Hourly distribution
hourly_orders = orders.groupby('hour').size()
axes[1, 0].bar(hourly_orders.index, hourly_orders.values, color='coral')
axes[1, 0].set_title('Orders by Hour of Day', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
axes[1, 0].set_xlabel('Hour')
axes[1, 0].set_ylabel('Number of Orders')
axes[1, 0].set_xticks(range(0, 24))

# Day of week distribution
dow_orders = orders.groupby('dayofweek').size()
dow_names = ['Mon', 'Tue', 'Wed', 'Thu', 'Fri', 'Sat', 'Sun']
axes[1, 1].bar(dow_names, dow_orders.values, color='lightgreen')
axes[1, 1].set_title('Orders by Day of Week', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
axes[1, 1].set_xlabel('Day')
axes[1, 1].set_ylabel('Number of Orders')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

print("\n Peak Shopping Hours:")
print(hourly_orders.sort_values(ascending=False).head())
print("\n Busiest Days:")
print(dow_orders.sort_values(ascending=False))

# Merge products with category translation
products_translated = products.merge(
    category_translation, 
    on='product_category_name', 
    how='left'
)

# Merge with order items to get sales data
product_sales = order_items.merge(
    products_translated[['product_id', 'product_category_name_english']], 
    on='product_id', 
    how='left'
)

# Top categories by volume
top_categories = product_sales['product_category_name_english'].value_counts().head(15)

fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(16, 6))

# Top 15 categories
axes[0].barh(range(len(top_categories)), top_categories.values, color='teal')
axes[0].set_yticks(range(len(top_categories)))
axes[0].set_yticklabels(top_categories.index)
axes[0].set_xlabel('Number of Orders')
axes[0].set_title('Top 15 Product Categories', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
axes[0].invert_yaxis()

# Category revenue
category_revenue = product_sales.groupby('product_category_name_english')['price'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False).head(15)

axes[1].set_yticks(range(len(category_revenue)))
axes[1].set_yticklabels(category_revenue.index)

# Calculate delivery times
orders['delivery_time'] = (orders['order_delivered_customer_date'] - 
                           orders['order_purchase_timestamp']).dt.days
orders['estimated_delivery_time'] = (orders['order_estimated_delivery_date'] - 
                                     orders['order_purchase_timestamp']).dt.days
orders['delivery_delay'] = orders['delivery_time'] - orders['estimated_delivery_time']

# Filter delivered orders
delivered_orders = orders[orders['order_status'] == 'delivered'].copy()

fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(16, 10))

# Actual delivery time distribution
axes[0, 0].hist(delivered_orders['delivery_time'].dropna(), bins=50, color='skyblue', edgecolor='black')
axes[0, 0].set_title('Actual Delivery Time Distribution', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
axes[0, 0].set_xlabel('Delivery Time (days)')
axes[0, 0].set_ylabel('Frequency')
axes[0, 0].axvline(delivered_orders['delivery_time'].median(), color='red', 
                   linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {delivered_orders["delivery_time"].median():.1f} days')
axes[0, 0].legend()

# Estimated vs Actual
axes[0, 1].scatter(delivered_orders['estimated_delivery_time'], 
                   delivered_orders['delivery_time'], alpha=0.3, s=5)
axes[0, 1].plot([0, 60], [0, 60], 'r--', label='Perfect estimate')
axes[0, 1].set_title('Estimated vs Actual Delivery Time', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
axes[0, 1].set_xlabel('Estimated Delivery Time (days)')
axes[0, 1].set_ylabel('Actual Delivery Time (days)')
axes[0, 1].set_xlim(0, 60)
axes[0, 1].set_ylim(0, 60)
axes[0, 1].legend()

# Delivery delay distribution
axes[1, 0].hist(delivered_orders['delivery_delay'].dropna(), bins=50, color='coral', edgecolor='black')
axes[1, 0].set_title('Delivery Delay Distribution', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
axes[1, 0].set_xlabel('Delay (days, negative = early)')
axes[1, 0].set_ylabel('Frequency')
axes[1, 0].axvline(0, color='green', linestyle='--', label='On time')
axes[1, 0].legend()

# On-time delivery rate by month
delivered_orders['on_time'] = delivered_orders['delivery_delay'] <= 0
monthly_on_time = delivered_orders.groupby(['year', 'month'])['on_time'].mean() * 100
axes[1, 1].plot(range(len(monthly_on_time)), monthly_on_time.values, marker='o', linewidth=2)
axes[1, 1].set_title('On-Time Delivery Rate Over Time', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
axes[1, 1].set_xlabel('Month')
axes[1, 1].set_ylabel('On-Time Rate (%)')
axes[1, 1].axhline(monthly_on_time.mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', 
                   label=f'Average: {monthly_on_time.mean():.1f}%')
axes[1, 1].legend()
axes[1, 1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
